description: We are seeking an experienced AI/ML developer to create a custom solution that unifies the artistic style across multiple AI-generated images (from Midjourney, DALL-E, etc.). The end goal is to produce images that share the same “brushstroke” style and can be upscaled for large-format printing (e.g., 4 ft x 4 ft) without losing quality.### Project Scope & Deliverables:1. Neural Style Transfer Implementation- Develop or fine-tune a model (PyTorch or TensorFlow) to apply a consistent “oil painting” style across diverse images.- Ensure stylistic consistency for different scenes or subjects (e.g., portraits, landscapes).2. High-Resolution Upscaling- Implement state-of-the-art super-resolution techniques (e.g., ESRGAN or Real-ESRGAN) to preserve detail at large sizes (A0, A1, or 4 ft x 4 ft).- Maintain clarity and texture fidelity after upscaling.3. Customization & Ownership- We will provide reference/style images and test data.- We require full ownership of the final program and source code (including the final trained model/checkpoints).4. Integration & Ease of Use- Ideally deliver a user-friendly script or small application that can accept new images and process them automatically.- Provide clear documentation for setup and usage.### Additional Details:- Timeline: Sooner is better. Please share your estimated turnaround time.- Budget: Flexible; open to discussing either fixed-price or hourly.- Communication: Must be comfortable discussing scope and providing progress updates.- Required Expertise:- Deep learning frameworks (PyTorch/TensorFlow)- Neural style transfer (Gatys-style NST, FastNST, LoRA, or custom approach)- Super-resolution/upscaling (ESRGAN, Real-ESRGAN, or similar)- Image processing & computer vision best practices- GPU-based development experience is a plusIf you have a proven track record in AI-driven image manipulation, style transfer, or upscaling for print, we’d love to see examples of your work or portfolio.
skills: ai,dall-e api,deep learning,image processing,midjourney ai,neural network,tensorflow
title: Neural Style Transfer & High-Resolution Image Upscaling Developer Needed

company_description: The Norwegian Refugee Council (NRC) is an independent humanitarian organisation helping people forced to flee.We protect displaced people and support them as they build a new future. We started our relief efforts after World War Two. Today, we work in both new and protracted crises across 40 countries. We specialise in six areas: food security, education, shelter, legal assistance, protection from violence, and water, sanitation and hygiene.We stand up for people forced to flee. NRC is a determined advocate for displaced people. We promote and defend displaced people's rights and dignity in local communities, with national governments and in the international arena. NRC’s Internal Displacement Monitoring Centre in Geneva is a global leader in monitoring, reporting on and advocating for people displaced within their own country.We work with partners across the world through NORCAP, our global provider of humanitarian, development and peacebuilding expertise. NORCAP collaborates with local, national and international partners on finding sustainable solutions to meet the needs of people at risk.Around 15,000 humanitarians work with the NRC. Most of us are hired locally to work in the field, and a small number are based at our head office in Oslo. Many of our colleagues were once themselves forced to flee their homes.NRC assisted almost 10 million people worldwide in 2023, and with your support, we can help even more.In order to meet the needs of 117 million displaced people worldwide, we need to unite forces across sectors and work together as one team. Through mutual partnerships we are dedicated to finding unique solutions for people who have been forced to flee, helping them build a sustainable future for themselves and their communities.To find out how you can support our work, please visit nrc.no/corporate or send an e-mail to corporate@nrc.no.
